page.title: 04WILDLIFE
page.content: In the village of{Northend}there are lots of places where animal homes might be because there are lots of trees and fields.Behind{Northend}there are some hills with quarries and woods.There are quite a lot of ponds and streams in the village as well. There are old badger sets by the side of the road up the hills.In the village of{Gaydon}there are not so many places because{Gaydon}is bigger and more noiser there are some ponds lots of fields and a few woods.In winter farmers put bags of oats and food for the animals but combine harvesters soon reck their homes. Tractors plough fields up and distroy nests.Men chop trees down and distroy homes of insects and animals.
